<item>
            <title>[JDK-8329261] G1: interpreter post-barrier x86 code asserts index size of wrong buffer</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8329261</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The following assertion within G1BarrierSetAssembler::g1_write_barrier_post() in src/hotspot/cpu/x86/gc/g1/g1BarrierSetAssembler_x86.cpp:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
// Generated code assumes that buffer index is pointer sized.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;STATIC_ASSERT(in_bytes(SATBMarkQueue::byte_width_of_index()) == sizeof(intptr_t));&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
refers to the size of the index of the SATBMarkQueue buffer, which is unused in the post-barrier. It should probably refer instead to G1DirtyCardQueue::byte_width_of_index().&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This issue was found by [~kbarrett].</description>
